## API Endpoints and Implementation Methods

**HTTP API v2 Integration:**
```
POST /2/httpapi
```
- Server-side session tracking via session_id field in event payloads
- Custom session property definition and real-time tracking
- Bulk event ingestion with session boundary management

**Chart Configuration Parameters:**
- **Count Dropdown Options:** Event Count, Session Duration, Session Frequency, Time-based metrics
- **Segment By Module:** Property-based analysis with multi-dimensional segmentation
- **Measurement Types:** Total Sessions, Time Spent per User, Average Length, Length Distribution, Average Per User, Average Events per Sessions, Total Events Across Sessions

**Filter Implementation:**
- **Session Duration Filters** - Time-based session qualification with customizable thresholds
- **Contains Event Filters** - Session qualification based on specific event presence
- **Page URL Filtering** - URL pattern matching with contains operators
- **Conversion Event Filtering** - Add to Cart, Purchase, and custom conversion event tracking

**Command Line and Configuration:**
- Session timeout configuration for mobile (5 minutes) and web (30 minutes) platforms
- Custom session property mapping and event assignment rules
- Automated session boundary detection algorithm configuration

The User Sessions module represents a sophisticated behavioral analytics solution that transforms traditional event-based analysis into comprehensive session-centric insights, enabling organizations to understand user engagement patterns while maintaining seamless integration with Amplitude's comprehensive analytics platform architecture.